		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Sure, but unless I can make the inner loops similar enough to be switched based on a variable, it would involve having both loops in the code, and thus more complexity. It's already complex enough to follow as it is. I'll take a look though, since it would be nice to have one ROM.
<br />
<br />I came across your vertical stretch demo where you blend lines via flickering. I realized that this would benefit the smooth gradient version of this palette demo. Since it already shakes horizontally at 30 Hz, effectively blending the vertical edges, I could have it shake vertically as well, blending it all together more.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


