	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">blargg wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Sure, but unless I can make the inner loops similar enough to be switched based on a variable, it would involve having both loops in the code, and thus more complexity. It's already complex enough to follow as it is.</div>
<br />For each mode, make a 32-entry table of tints and a 32-entry table of starting colors. Order them in ROM as normal_tints, smooth_tints, normal_startcolors, smooth_startcolors. Then display entries 0-31 or 32-63 of each table.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
